  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Acute kidney injury (AKI) is a common clinical syndrome, especially in the hospital patients.
      AKI is recognized as an important risk factor for incident chronic kidney disease,
      accelerated progression to end-stage renal disease,and increased risk of short-term and
      long-term mortality.This study is to observe the prognosis of hospitalized patients with AKI
      in China.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
